ble on `/v1/evidence/cutover-report.chainOfCustody`. They trace source registry events, scheduled runs, raw captures, hashed object refs, extraction deltas, claim-ledger review, graph relationships, API/search snapshots, and STIX export previews with ids, hashes, timestamps, parser versions, confidence, review state, retention/redaction state, replay cursors, and stage links only. They must fail or hold on missing captures, stale/missing object refs, broken hash chains, parser-version drift, cursor replay gaps, export-without-review, restricted-body presence, and redaction repair needs while never exposing raw bodies, object keys, unsafe URLs, restricted material, secrets, credentials, or actor-interaction content. - `/v1/intel/search` exposes `analystLoop` and `tiExperience` as the UI-ready state projection for `/ti`: `queued`, `metadata_review`, `blocked_unsafe_target`, `needs_source_activation`, or `ready`, with visible next steps, safe metadata claims, source gaps, polling, redacted notification context, and source activation approval workflows. Metadata review cards and inbox rows should include a UI-ready `claimHeadline` such as "Company X leaked, 50k accounts, 20 GB" plus explicit verification-boundary text; victim notification UI packets should include `redactedNotification`; source activation UI packets should include `approvalWorkflow`; these fields must remain metadata-only and must not imply verified leaked-data access or source activation. Run clarity must count approval-only work, blocked unsafe targets, metadata-review rows, notification drafts, and claim-ledger rows as meaningful work so the UI never collapses metadata-only analyst work into "0 queued tasks". `analystLoop.workQueue` and `tiExperience.workQueue` should provide a single UI-renderable, priority-ordered queue across queued collection, metadata review, blocked unsafe targets, source activation approvals, victim notification drafts, and claim-ledger review items with route/action hints, sa