on decisions. - `src/registry/sourceRegistry.ts`: in-memory registry interface and implementation. - `src/frontier/frontier.ts`: focused crawler scoring and queue. - `src/adapters/*`: first adapter interfaces and safe placeholders. - `src/pipeline/*`: extraction and incident candidate pipeline. - `src/storage/memoryStore.ts`: test/dev storage. - `src/api/server.ts`: Bun HTTP API. ## Main-Agent Monitor Log - 2026-06-20 13:59 CEST Agent 10 completed the first Program BG live product SLO/revenue telemetry slice and remains active on the longer-running operations vision. `GET /v1/ops/product-slo` now exposes `ti.live_product_slo_dashboard.v1` with fixture/local/Inspur/public proof mode, first-response p95, 3-second polling, first fresh evidence latency, source freshness, claim-cluster yield, empty-result honesty, Actor run success, rows/useful rows per query, cost per useful row when cost inputs exist, queue age, memory, disk growth, deployment proof ids, and 96 GB/160 GB/500 GB/browser-disabled/no-GPU guardrails. Daily snapshots are append-only JSONL and the 7-day Apify launch model keeps unknown users/revenue/cost metrics null instead of invented. The route is in route inventory and ops contract semantics; operations docs document thresholds, snapshot path, and proof commands. Verification is green for `bun run check`, focused ops/API/source-seed tests, `bun run check:route-inventory`, `bun run check:contract-index`, `bun run measure:search-product`, and full `bun test` (519 pass). Next Agent 10 work is live public/Inspur proof capture, real daily snapshots, and 7-day launch observation. - 2026-05-24 23:20 CEST Agent 10 completed Program BF value-program operations soak proof and is ready for the next operations task. `ti.cutover.soak_release_packet.v1` now includes `valueProgramOpsSoak` with schema `ti.value_program.ops_soak.v1`, covering 24h refresh-soak gates for the 60k dark-web metadata refresh and 10k source-atlas import, side-tool resource budgets, public-searc